snippet.title: EVERTON 1-1 TOTTENHAM | Premier League highlights
snippet.description:
Another spirited display didnâ€™t look to be enough when Abdoulaye Doucoue was shown a straight red card just before the hour mark for a shove on Harry Kane, before the England striker netted from the penalty spot minutes later after Keane has brought down Cristian Romero.

But Everton refused to give in. And after piling on the pressure despite the numerical disadvantage, a straight red card for substitute Lucas Moura for a late challenge on Keane two minutes from time offered a lifeline.

Keane then turned hero in dramatic fashion, smashing a superb 25-yard drive past Hugo Lloris to spark jubilant scenes around Goodison.
